VALUES ('B2_U15_B1_I1', 'ingles-b2-U15', 1, 'fill_blanks', 'Complete each sentence with the correct perfect modal verb.', '{"prompt_es":"Complete each sentence with the correct perfect modal verb.","mastery_tag":"grammar:b2-perfect-modals","main_text":"She ___ (not/attend) the meeting; I didn''t see her there.","correct_answer":["must not have attended","should have arrived","could have called","should have told","must have finished"],"explanation":"(1) Usamos ''must not have'' para indicar una conclusión lógica sobre algo que no ocurrió.\n(2) Utilizamos ''should have'' para expresar una expectativa que no se cumplió.\n(3) Aquí, ''could have'' indica una posibilidad que no se realizó.\n(4) ''Should have told'' indica que era correcto o recomendable informar.\n(5) Usamos ''must have finished'' para suponer que algo tuvo que ocurrir.","complexity":3,"concept_tags":["grammar","perfect","modals","unit"]}')
